Spring Boot follows the maven directory sturcutre.
    src\main\java - java code.
    src\main\resources - config files used by our application.
    src\test\java - unit testing source code.


MAVEN WRAPPER FILES:
mvnw and mvnw.cmd are maven wrapper files without installing maven.
This automatically downloads the correct version.



MAVEN POM FILE:
    1. This is a collection of dependencies, however, when using Spring Boot
    this takes care of the hustle.
    	<dependency>
    			<groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
    			<artifactId>spring-boot-starter-web</artifactId>
    	</dependency>
    2. This is a maven plugin so we can apply two commands in here.
        mvnw package and mvnw spring-boot: run.
        <plugin>
        		<groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
        		<artifactId>spring-boot-maven-plugin</artifactId>
        </plugin>